{
  "stem": "11771.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Till 1939 was going on, like it was going on years before, for hundreds years or more-- Ejszyszki was in existence, like according to the history of Ejszyszki, for thousands years-- Jewish life in Ejszyszki.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was, that time, a young-- a young boy, 13-years-old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we feel it also not only hearing it about in the radio, in the-- in the press, but also German refugees start to come in-- in-- when they were telling what's happening in Germany.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was-- is so close, so just a couple hundred miles away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was so far from us, that it's not going to happen here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the life was going on very normal.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then when the war break out with Poland, our region was taken over from the Russian.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they-- they gave it over to the Lithuanian, because Ejszyszki was before the first world war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It belonged to Lithuanian today.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they give it over to the Lithuanian.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But life wasn't change.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In-- and Jewish life, particularly, wasn't changed any difference from like it was when-- under the Polish regime.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we didn't feel, actually, any difference.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And eight months later, the Russian took it over-- Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They occupied Lithuanian again.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we were a part, like a Lithuanian Republic of Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In '40-- 1940, shortly after the second world war start.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were all living, I would say, in peaceful manners, till the second world war-- till June 22nd, 1941, when Hitler decide to occupied Russia, in particular, not even declare war on Russia.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were occupied the second day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The 23rd was the first Russian soldiers came in into our city.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the army flew so fast eastward-- like nobody stops him.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
